@NODE Release_Notes "Release Notes"
Release 37.00  ( 09-Jun-94 )

- Initial Release.

Release 37.10  ( 01-Jan-95 )

- changed GUI to include new features and controls
- added online help facility thru AmigaGuide
- replaced "view" feature with real-time brush adjustment
- can now save over the original brush, the program no longer
  holds it open
- chunk found in original brush should now appear in saved brush
  some non-standard chunks may not appear

@ENDNODE

@NODE Introduction "Introduction"
This program loads an IFF ILBM brush file and allows the user to
adjust/set the BMHD's (BitMapHeader) "x" and "y" co-ordinates. These
are the offsets from the top left hand corner of the original bitmap.

I put this tool together when I found out that DeluxePaint® does not
store the x/y offset of a saved brush. ( nor does it read it )


@ENDNODE

@NODE System_Requirements "System Requirements"
     Required:

     - Workbench 2.04+

     Optional:

     - reqtools.library (version 38 or higher)


@ENDNODE

