@NODE Using_the_Workbench "Using the Workbench"
To install "BrushXY" onto your system drag the "BrushXY" and
"BrushXY.guide" icons into the "tools" drawer on your system disk.

You may also with to drag the icons for "Diver.pic", "Diver1.win",
and "Diver2.win" into the "tools" drawer as well.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Using_the_CLI "Using the CLI"
Use the Workbench its easier.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Tooltypes "Tooltypes"
At present only the following tooltypes are supported.

PUBSCREEN=<public-screen-name>

This is the name of the public screen you wish "BrushXY" to
open its window on. Defaults to the Workbench.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Instructions "Instructions"
@{" Starting and Stopping " Link Starting_and_Stopping}
@{" Toolbox window " Link Toolbox_window}
@{" Graphics window " Link Graphics_window}
@{" Keyboard Equivalents " Link Keyboard_Equivalents}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Starting_and_Stopping "Starting and Stopping"
To run "BrushXY" simply double click on its icon and the program
will start. You may also specify a brush to work on at this time
by clicking once on then brush's icon then holding down the shift key 
clicking twice on "BrushXY"'s icon. This will cause the program to
load up the brush when it starts.

When the program starts it will display the @{" Toolbox window " Link Toolbox_window} on
either the default public screen or the one you specified in
@{" Tooltypes " Link Tooltypes}. This window's @{" Gadgets " Link Gadgets} and @{" Menus " Link Menus} allow you to
load, save, and manipulate brushes.

Once you load a brush or a background the @{" Graphics window " Link Graphics_window} will
then be opened on a custom screen, compatible with the brush or
background you loaded, for the graphic to be displayed, and the
@{" Toolbox window " Link Toolbox_window} will move to this custom screen.

To terminate "BrushXY" either select the @{" Quit " Link Quit} gadget or menu item.
If you close the @{" Toolbox window " Link Toolbox_window} when no graphics are currently
begin displayed this will also terminate the program.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Toolbox_window "Toolbox window"
The Toolbox window contains the @{" Gadgets " Link Gadgets} and @{" Menus " Link Menus} you will need
to load, save, and manipulate brushes. Many of these tools also have 
@{" Keyboard Equivalents " Link Keyboard_Equivalents}.

@{" Gadgets " Link Gadgets}
@{" Menus " Link Menus}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Gadgets "Gadgets"
"X and Y Sliders"
     These allow you to quickly adjust the x/y co-ords of the brush.

"Arrow Buttons"
     These allow you to make fine adjustments to the x/y co-ords of
     the brush. The single arrows adjust ± 1 pixel while the double
     arrows adjust ± 10 pixels.

"Close Window Gadget"
     This will close the Toolbox window, and if there is no brush
     or background currently load it will also terminate the program.

"Back"         See @{" Load Background " Link Load_Background} menu item.

"Brush"        See @{" Load Brush " Link Load_Brush} menu item.

"Save"         See @{" Save Brush " Link Save_Brush} menu item.

"Save as"      See @{" Save Brush as " Link Save_Brush_as} menu item.

"New"          See @{" New " Link New} menu item.

"Info"         See @{" Info " Link Info} menu item.

"HELP!"        See @{" HELP! " Link HELP!} menu item.

"Quit"         See @{" Quit " Link Quit} menu item.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus "Menus"
@{" New " Link New}
@{" Load Background " Link Load_Background}
@{" Load Brush " Link Load_Brush}
@{" Save Brush " Link Save_Brush}
@{" Save Brush as " Link Save_Brush_as}
