@NODE New "New"
Clears any loaded brush or background closes the @{" Graphics window " Link Graphics_window}
and returns the Toolbox window to the public screen.

If unsaved changes exist a confimation requester will ask for
permission to proceed. If you reply "Okay" to this requester any
unsaved changes will be lost.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Load_Background "Load Background"
Brings up a file requester from which you can select an ILBM file
to use as a background. If you load a background its colours
will be used instead of any brush you load, unless you select the
@{" Brush Palette " Link Brush_Palette} option.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Load_Brush "Load Brush"
Brings up a file requester from which you can select the ILBM file
file you wish to use as a brush.

If unsaved changes to a current brush exist a confimation requester
will ask for permission to proceed. If you reply "Okay" to this
requester any unsaved changes will be lost.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Save_Brush "Save Brush"
Allows you to save any changes you make to the brush you previously
loaded. If the file exists a confirmation requester will ask for
permission to overwrite it. If you have selected the @{" Overwrite " Link Overwrite}
option no confirmation is requested.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Save_Brush_as "Save Brush as"
Brings up a file requester from which you can select a file to save
the brush to. If the file exists a confirmation requester will ask
for permission to overwrite it. If you have selected the @{" Overwrite " Link Overwrite}
option no confirmation is requested.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Info "Info"
Displays info about the currently loaded brush.

@ENDNODE

@NODE HELP! "HELP!"
Opens "BrushXY.guide" to the "Instructions" page.

The guide will always open on the default public screen.

@ENDNODE

@NODE About "About"
Displays information about "BrushXY".

@ENDNODE

@NODE Quit "Quit"
Exits "BrushXY". If unsaved changes exist, a confirmation requester
will ask for permission to quit. If you answer "Okay" to this 
requester any unsaved changes will be lost.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Brush_Palette "Brush Palette"
Instructs the program to use the palette of the current brush over
that of the background.

DEFAULT: OFF

@ENDNODE

@NODE Create_Icons "Create Icons"
Instructs the program to save an icon along with any saved brush file.
If an icon already exists for a file it is left intact.

DEFAULT: ON

@ENDNODE

@NODE Overwrite "Overwrite"
Instructs the program to overwrite an existing file and not ask for
permission to do so.

DEFAULT: OFF

@ENDNODE

@NODE Toolbox "Toolbox"
Opens the @{" Toolbox window " Link Toolbox_window} if it isn't already open. This option
has no effect unless the @{" Graphics window " Link Graphics_window} is also open. If the
@{" Graphics window " Link Graphics_window} is closed then closing the @{" Toolbox window " Link Toolbox_window} would
terminate the program.

DEFAULT: ON

@ENDNODE

@NODE Save_Settings "Save Settings"
Saves the options, current brush path, current file pattern, and the
current @{" Toolbox window " Link Toolbox_window} position to the "BrushXY.prefs" file. This
file is kept in the "ENV:BrushXY" and "ENVARC:BrushXY" directories.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Graphics_window "Graphics window"
The Graphics window displays the currently loaded brush plus over a
background graphic, if the user has loaded one. When the user uses
one of the brush adjustment tools the brush will move about the window.

The brush is limited to the confines of the window, and no part of it
may be moved outside of the window.

The @{" Toolbox window " Link Toolbox_window} can also appear on this screen, and always in
front of the Graphics window. If the toolbox is getting in your way
you can always close it by either clicking on its close gadget or
selecting the @{" Toolbox " Link Toolbox} menu item. To reopen toolbox simply select
the @{" Toolbox " Link Toolbox} menu item again. While the toolbox is closed you can
use the tools' @{" Keyboard Equivalents " Link Keyboard_Equivalents}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Keyboard_Equivalents "Keyboard Equivalents"
All the @{" Gadgets " Link Gadgets} and @{" Menus " Link Menus} have a keyboard equivalent.

Key(s)              Function
---------           ---------------
right-cursor        move brush 1 pixel right
left-cursor         move brush 1 pixel left
up-cursor           move brush 1 pixel up
down-cursor         move brush 1 pixel down
shift right-cursor  move brush 10 pixels right
shift left-cursor   move brush 10 pixels left
shift up-cursor     move brush 10 pixels up
shift down-cursor   move brush 10 pixels down
ctrl right-cursor   move brush to far right
ctrl left-cursor    move brush to far left
ctrl up-cursor      move brush to far top
ctrl down-cursor    move brush to far bottom
R-Amiga N           @{" New " Link New}
R-Amiga B           @{" Load Background " Link Load_Background}
R-Amiga L           @{" Load Brush " Link Load_Brush}
R-Amiga S           @{" Save Brush " Link Save_Brush}
R-Amiga A           @{" Save Brush as " Link Save_Brush_as}
R-Amiga I           @{" Info " Link Info}
Help                @{" HELP! " Link HELP!}
R-Amiga ?           @{" About " Link About}
R-Amiga Q           @{" Quit " Link Quit}
R-Amiga B           @{" Brush Palette " Link Brush_Palette}
R-Amiga C           @{" Create Icons " Link Create_Icons}
R-Amiga O           @{" Overwrite " Link Overwrite}
R-Amiga T           @{" Toolbox " Link Toolbox}
R-Amiga K           @{" Save Settings " Link Save_Settings}


@ENDNODE

@NODE Demo "Demo"
Included with this program are three ILBM's to demonstrate "BrushXY".

Diver.pic

This is a background graphic. If you load this you will note that there
is a blacked out area in the center. This is where the brush was taken
from.

Diver1.win

This is the brush saved directly from DeluxePaint. If you load this
you will see that it is displayed in the upper left hand corner of
the display, not where it was originally made. This is because
DeluxePaint does not save the x/y co-ordinates, but instead sets them
to zero on write and ignores them on read.

Diver2.win

This is the brush that has been adjusted through "BrushXY". If you
load this you will see that it is display in the correct position.
If you have also loaded the background then the brush neatly fills
in the blacked out area.


@ENDNODE

